metadata.name: Tangled #108
metadata.description:
"Tangled" is a generative art project that explores the emergent behaviour of simple shapes moving according to a random flow field. While the final result is always constrained to the shape of a circle, the variation within is endless.

Instructions:
Press "p" to pause the animation.
In live mode, press 1 through 5 to save a PNG version of the final result. The following resolutions are available:
1: 400 x 400 (ideal for Twitter PFP)
2: 1000 x 1000
3: 2000 x 2000
4: 4000 x 4000
5: 5000 x 5000
Please be patient, generating the PNG may take some time!

Made with p5.js.

metadata.name: Ersbla #310
metadata.description:
Ersbla is part of the fxhash live minting experience at Proof of People, London 2022. 

It is the third entry in a series of abstract generative experiments inspired by the graphic and textile work of Anni and Josef Albers. As a follow-up to the 'Sabler' and 'Lebras' collections, 'Ersbla' produces textile effects using a combination of thousands of tiny dots arranged on variable grids, resulting in a wide variety of unique Bauhaus-inspired compositions in a variety of palettes.

Press 'S' to save a high-resolution 2400 x 3396 px image in PNG format.

Depending on the density of your output, please allow up to a few seconds for your edition to generate.

metadata.name: Shifted Blocks #1
metadata.description:
The art is programmatically drawn using basic shapes, math, random using p5js.

To save image:

press '0' || 'd' to save image is default quality
press '1' || 's' to save image as '613x775px'
press '2' || 'm' to save image as '735x930px'
press '3' to save image as '883x1116px'
press '4' || 'p' to save image as '1059x1339px'
press '5' to save image as '1271x1607px'
press '6' to save image as '1525x1928px'
press '7' || 'h' to save image as '1831x2314px'

press 'f' to see art in full screen.

created by: https://twitter.com/mrmecroni or NotaArtist

metadata.name: Lines of Solitude #24
metadata.description:
There is a mystery in the lifeline, where we walk and discover all alone. Some landscapes make we breath this solitude.

- 17 palettes available.
- 2 Styles of landscapes (Desert and Sea).
- 2 Colors of Sea (Red and Blue).
- The Desert may contain cactus.

Press the [S] key in live view to save a "Lines of solitude".jpg file.

This artwork was created with p5.js

Collab: Nobody (@jorgemauro1000) and Ad Mortem Festinamus (@AFestinamus).

metadata.name: Gradient Ascent #48
metadata.description:
Generates a lo-fi sci-fi landscape and applies effects to the result. Most are 2:3 portrait aspect ratio with a smaller chance for landscape or square.

Several cool bonus features are included. Click to draw the image without post processing which can also be downloaded. The unique effect for each iteration can be applied to any image, just drag and drop! There are also URL commands included for advanced users.

Controls

Click = Toggle Processing
Drag & Drop = Process an Image
1 = Toggle processing
2 = Increase resolution
3 = Save as a png

URL Commands

width and height = Change the output size
hd = Set to 1 to show HD by default

Programmed in Vanilla JavaScript by KilledByAPixel
Code and Outputs are Copyright (C) 2022 Frank Force
Artwork is released under CC BY-NC 4.0
